Description: Sing Hat Company uses the finest quality beaver furs.
Full Description: Christy Sing Robertson grew up in the Ozarks of Arkansas and moved to Jackson, Wyoming in 2003 to work for a summer at Lost Creek Ranch. She, like so many others in Jackson, never planned to stay long term. But after returning home, Christy found herself with a longing for the mountains that she couldn’t shake. So, on January 1, 2005 she moved for good. Christy now calls the Tetons home where she lives in a cabin at the base of Munger Mountain with her two children and their dog, Charlotte. Sing Hat Company was founded out of a love for the western lifestyle and landscape. Drawing from her heritage of rodeo cowboy uncles, a farming grandfather, and an ever deepening connection to the land around her, Sing set out to learn more about hat making and to fill a need in her beloved Jackson Hole. Sing Hat Company uses the finest quality beaver furs made in the USA. Our hats are timeless, custom made works of art, tailored to fit your personal style. Whether ranching, adventuring in the wild, or heading to a beer joint or honky tonk a custom Sing Hat will have you covered.

Ebix Health provides technology solutions for employee benefits management. It offers LuminX, an automated system designed for
Full Description: Ebix Health provides technology solutions for employee benefits management. It offers LuminX, an automated system designed for organizations to administer health and other employee benefits. The company provides Absence Management LX, which includes short-term disability and long-term disability blocks that provide eligibility, billing and remittance of claims, integrated document scanning and storage, and remote access; and Consumer LX solution to manage flexible spending accounts, health reimbursement accounts, and health savings accounts. Its products also include Dental/Vision LX solution to handle the administration of dental and vision coverage; Health LX to handle the eligibility, adjudication, billing, and remittance of claims in various health insurance plans; and Insurance LX solution that includes group life, and accidental death and disbursement products. In addition, the company offers Web tools, such as online enrollment; advanced reporting and business intelligence; accounting capabilities; plan modeling capabilities; integrated technologies; and outsourcing services. It serves insurance carriers, health plans, third party administrators, plan sponsors, brokers, and self-administered organizations. The company has strategic partnerships with AdminiSource; Bloodhound; Captiva; CareVu; Coalition America, Inc.; Emdeon Business Services; Evolution Benefits, Inc.; Ingenix; JMS & Associates; MBI Benefits; MCFG; NHBC; Preferred Medical Claim Solutions; PHX; PPHA; SOCRATES, INC.; TC3; and The Phia Group, LLC. Ebix Health was formerly known as Acclamation Systems, Inc. and changed its name to Ebix Health in August 2008. Ebix Health was founded in 1989 and is based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. As of August 1, 2008, Ebix Health operates as a subsidiary of Ebix Inc.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: ( ICT ) or ""In Circuit Test"" is the one and only industry standard that is used at the end of every assembly line everywhere in the world. Its function is to electrically stimulate the circuitry of an assembled circuit board to PASS / FAIL “and” identify any failures as a product reaches the end of a line. The more complex a design, the higher the failure rate and the more ICT becomes a company’s only practical solution to verify the 2 to 12% typical failure rate.The biggest problem companies having with ICT is the cost of the test fixtures that make the mechanical connection between the equipment and the assembled board.  The traditional solutions that all companies buy today have been made exactly the same as they were 35 years ago. And the reason there has been zero innovations to fix the problem, is because compamies like Agilent ( HP ) & Teradyne who control most of the global market couldnt change the mechanical designs of the equipment interface because new introductions had to be able to support the existing fixtures and files customers already owned. The GameChanger is the first of a new generation that solves the big issue every company has complained about for many year

Description: SaaS: Your white-labeled, project management solution providing smart automation and real-time reporting.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: While there are several alternatives in the market today none can support both product and project management with ease. More often it is easier for teams to utilize excel to manage a project but there is a lack of connectivity to a kanban board and there quickly becomes reporting gaps. Further, when technology is deployed to manage projects, the administrative tasks often lead to additional frustration or worse a failed initiative. Additionally, while we love kanban boards, during time spent at Harvard University, Cornell University, Indiana University, and Western Governors University we evaluated modern work management and technology. What we found was while there are many alternatives, none focused on the user experience but rather approached work from a singular methodology and has limitations as complexity grows. ProjectBIOS is the first human focused technology that: - Enables best practices from the Project Management Institute, Management & Strategy Institute, Harvard University, Cornell University, Indiana University, and Western Governors University including but not limited to managing inputs and outputs such as requirements and mockups as inputs with acceptance criteria and testing evidence as outputs. - Supports waterfall, agile, and hybrid approaches within the same workstream. - Focuses on delivering benefits by nesting the inputs/outputs and process required instead of the traditional approach to list the individual steps resulting in unclear status of the expected benefits outlined in the project charter. - Provides the ability to stack projects, programs, portfolios, and product development into a singular view with unified, real-time reporting. - Allows the user to see their list of deliverables across all workstreams organized using best practices from the Project Management Institute to improve outcomes including but not limited to sorting the activities while considering priority, due date, progress and other important aspects. - Allows each team member to keep private notes and post public updates on each deliverable so that external lists, notes, or tools are no longer needed to provide a single source of truth. - Provides an integrated project plan for teams, clients, and third-parties while controlling which activities are available to be viewed and worked. - Is built to simplify complexity while empowering team members to succeed. - Will revolutionize work management including but not limited to risk management, resource management, process optimization, and client management through the use of artificial intelligence (AI).

Description: Hengye USA supplies industrial adsorbents such as molecular sieves, activated alumina, silica gels, ceramic balls, and zeolites.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Hengye USA supplies industrial adsorbents; The highest quality molecular sieves, activated alumina, silica gels, ceramic balls, and zeolites. 	 Hengye USA distributes and sells a variety of molecular sieves including Angstrom Molecular Sieves, Carbon, Zeolite, and Mesoporous. Molecular sieves are crystalline metal aluminosilicates having a three-dimensional interconnecting network of silica and alumina tetrahedra.  Natural water of hydration is removed from this network by heating to produce uniform cavities which selectively adsorb molecules of a specific size. A4 to 8-mesh sieve is normally used in gasphase applications, while the 8 to 12-mesh type is common in liquidphase applications. The powder forms of the 3A, 4A, 5A and 13X molecular sieves are suitable for specialized applications.  Long known for their drying capacity (even to 90Â°C), molecular sieves have recently demonstrated utility in synthetic organic procedures, frequently allowing isolation of desired products from condensation reactions that are governed by generally unfavorable equilibria.   These synthetic zeolites have been shown to remove water, alcohols (including methanol and ethanol), and HCl from such systems as ketimine and enamine syntheses, ester condensations, and the conversion of unsaturated aldehydes to polyenals.
